      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, though the records for the weather and harvest those years actually look pretty standard for the region. It's just so puzzling because the drop is so concentrated. I was wondering if there's any precedent for \"phantom populations\" in these kinds of historical documents—cases where the data suggests a presence or a void that doesn't have a clear physical or economic explanation?",
